The following step-by-step algorithm describes the complete flow of the Hospital Patient Management System:

Main Program Flow
1.	START
2.	Initialize patient array (patients[100]) and a waiting queue. Set count = 0.
3.	Display the MAIN MENU with options:    1. Add Patient    2. View Patients    3. Search Patient    4. Delete Patient    5. Exit
4.	Read user choice (integer input).
5.	Execute the operation corresponding to the choice (see sub-algorithms below).
6.	Repeat steps 3–5 in a do-while loop until the user selects option 5.
7.	Display "Exiting..." and STOP.

Sub-Algorithm: Add Patient (Choice 1)
8.	Check if count >= 100. If yes, display "Patient list is full!" and return.
9.	Prompt and read: Patient ID, Name, Age into patients[count].
10.	Push the Patient ID into waitingQueue.
11.	Increment count by 1.
12.	Display "Patient added successfully!" and return to main menu.

Sub-Algorithm: View Patients (Choice 2)
13.	If count == 0, display "No patients available!" and return.
14.	Iterate through patients[0] to patients[count-1].
15.	For each patient, display: ID, Name, Age.
16.	Return to main menu.

Sub-Algorithm: Search Patient (Choice 3)
17.	Prompt and read the Patient ID to search.
18.	Iterate through patients[0] to patients[count-1].
19.	If patients[i].id == entered ID, display Name and Age, then return.
20.	If no match found after full traversal, display "Patient not found!"
21.	Return to main menu.

Sub-Algorithm: Delete Patient (Choice 4)
22.	Prompt and read the Patient ID to delete.
23.	Iterate through patients[0] to patients[count-1].
24.	If patients[i].id == entered ID:
•	Shift all elements from index i+1 onward one position to the left.
•	Decrement count by 1.
•	Display "Patient deleted successfully!" and return.
25.	If no match found, display "Patient not found!"
26.	Return to main menu.
 
